claims:
Claims 1. A method, in a data processing system comprising at least one processor and at least one memory, the at least one memory comprising instructions executed by the at least one processor to cause the at least one processor to implement a healthcare analytics management system, the method comprising: developing, by a healthcare analytics development sub-system of the healthcare analytics management system, an analytics pipeline of a set of analytics assets based on a set of business needs for a healthcare analytics client and a healthcare analytics model based on the set of analytics assets and the set of business needs, wherein the healthcare analytics model links to the analytics pipeline; deploying, by a model deployment module of a healthcare analytics operation sub-system of the healthcare analytics management system, the healthcare analytics model on a set of computing devices of the selected healthcare consumer; responsive to a model monitoring module of the healthcare analytics operation sub-system detecting a performance deviation of the deployed healthcare analytics model for performance deviation from the set of business needs for the healthcare analytics client, determining, by a model feedback module of the healthcare analytics operation sub-system, improvement needs for the healthcare analytics model; feeding, by the model feedback module, the improvement needs back to the healthcare analytics development subsystem; and customizing, by the healthcare analytics development sub-system, the healthcare analytics model based on the improvement needs. 2. The method of claim 1 , wherein the set of analytics assets comprises one or more analytics assets from the group consisting of data quality and insights, cohort construction, feature construction, and prescriptive and predictive analytics. 3. The method of claim 1 , wherein deploying the healthcare analytics model further comprises verifying one or more of input data checks, performing input data configuration, performing input data preparation, verifying one or more runtime environment checks, or performing runtime configuration. 4. The method of claim 1 , further comprising storing the analytics pipeline in a versioned analytics pipeline repository, wherein the versioned analytics pipeline repository comprises reusable libraries and wherein the versioned analytics pipeline is annotated to indicate metadata. 5. The method of claim 4, wherein the versioned analytics pipeline repository captures at least one of: analytics assets; analytics workflow pipeline or dependency of assets; any meta/configuration data to support the workflow; or key performance indicators (KPIs) or output results along the workflow. 6. The method of claim 5, further comprising storing the healthcare analytics model in a versioned analytics model repository, wherein the versioned analytics model repository is annotated to indicate metadata. 7. The method of claim 6, wherein the model repository captures at least one of: metadata of input data requirements; metadata of runtime environment requirements; metadata of model parameters; or metadata of baseline model performance key performance indicators (KPIs). 8. The method of claim 6, further comprising exposing configuration parameters of the versioned analytics pipeline repository and the metadata of the versioned analytics model repository through an application programming interface. 9. The method of claim 1 , wherein determining improvement needs for the healthcare analytics model comprises determining a root cause of the performance deviation and determining a model improvement based on the performance deviation and the determined root cause. 10. The method of claim 9, wherein determining improvement needs for the healthcare analytics model further comprises determining a need level associated with the model improvement. 11. The method of claim 9, wherein determining improvement needs for the healthcare analytics model further comprises using continuous learning based on analytics or a machine learning model. 12. The method of claim 1 , wherein deploying the healthcare analytics model on the set of computing devices of the selected healthcare consumer comprises deploying an aggregation of a plurality of healthcare analytics models on the set of computing devices. 13. The method of claim 1 , wherein customizing the healthcare analytics model based on the improvement needs comprises modifying data inputs, features used to define populations, or key model parameters. 14. The method of claim 1 , wherein customizing the healthcare analytics model based on the improvement needs comprises reverting to a previous version of the healthcare analytics model. 15. A computer program product comprising a computer readable storage medium having a computer readable program stored therein, wherein the computer readable program, when executed on a computing device, causes the computing device to implement a healthcare analytics management system, wherein the computer readable program causes the computing device to: develop, by a healthcare analytics development sub-system of the healthcare analytics management system, an analytics pipeline of a set of analytics assets for a selected healthcare based on a set of business needs for a healthcare analytics client and a healthcare analytics model based on the set of analytics assets and the set of business needs, wherein the healthcare analytics model links to the analytics pipeline; deploy, by a model deployment module of a healthcare analytics operation sub-system of the healthcare analytics management system, the healthcare analytics model on a set of computing devices of the selected healthcare consumer; 

